MFAphDV5jxwrxQCLXB2ZqjCPFtUF_GQUE5ZH2GFTNwFl-xyT_3I_Ys-gcZLA&__tn__=C-R&paipv=0&eav=AfbuJAzxCdKFRYvUSLc7B8Go1WLTynmtCkVs-gTXxIlZ5045uTsX7vxieCjjHT2fJcI'}], None, None, '5548293381954197', ['5548293381954197'], False, 'Shafin Sayeduzzaman\u200eBangladesh Student Association SIUC (BSA)'])dict_values(['3315085218728890', 'Like every year, Center for International Education (CIE) is going to arrange International Education Week this November from 14-17. Last year, our former President bhai Shujon Mehedi Hasan and I got the opportunity to represent our country and culture in front of hundred of students. Mehedi bhai did an amazing job collecting all the pictures and artifacts. This was quite an experience. This time We want everyone to come, spend some time in Bangladesh table and share your valuable thoughts and opinions about Bangladesh. For more details please contact me or put a comment below. Thank You.\n\nCenter for International Education SIU is at Center for International Education SIU.\nNovember 17, 2021 at 12:06 PM · Carbondale ·\n\nPresent day Bengali language has evolved for over 1,300 years. Sumaiya Binta Islam, international student from Bangladesh, 🇧🇩 thinks that Bengali literature is rich and vast. “Our poetry expresses a strong connection with nature, human rights, and resistance. People from Bangladesh fought for their right to speak their own language, so, as I use it, I remind myself of the history of struggle that many people went through in order to ensure we could enjoy this right today”. In the third picture, Sumaiya shows a card that reads "My beloved country, I love you the most" in Bengali. Sumaiya will continue to take part in #IEW2021 representing Bangladesh. #IEW2021 will take place at CIE for two more days, Wednesday and Thursday. Come take a look', 'Like every year, Center for International Education (CIE) is going to arrange International Education Week this November from 14-17. Last year, our former President bhai Shujon Mehedi Hasan and I got the opportunity to represent our country and culture in front of hundred of students. Mehedi bhai did an amazing job collecting all the pictures and artifacts. This was quite an experience. This time We want everyone to come, spend some time in Bangladesh table and share your valuable thoughts and opinions about Bangladesh. For more details please contact me or put a comment below. Thank You.', 'Center for International Education SIU is at Center for International Education SIU.\nNovember 17, 2021 at 12:06 PM · Carbondale ·\n\nPresent day Bengali language has evolved for over 1,300 years. Sumaiya Binta Islam, international student from Bangladesh, 🇧🇩 thinks that Bengali literature is rich and vast. “Our poetry expresses a strong connection with nature, human rights, and resistance. People from Bangladesh fought for their right to speak their own language, so, as I use it, I remind myself of the history of struggle that many people went through in order to ensure we could enjoy this right today”. In the third picture, Sumaiya shows a card that reads "My beloved country, I love you the most" in Bengali. Sumaiya will continue to take part in #IEW2021 representing Bangladesh. #IEW2021 will take place at CIE for two more days, Wednesday and Thursday. Come take a look', None, datetime.datetime(2022, 11, 3, 10, 43, 43), 1667490223, 'https://scontent-ord5-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/242353138_4860729567310795_4549382895650819283_n.jpg?stp=cp0_dst-jpg_e15_fr_q65&_nc_cat=102&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=5f2048&efg=eyJpIjoidCJ9&_nc_ohc=4i5MvpdXIisAX8fQJ7-&_nc_ht=scontent-ord5-2.xx&oh=00_AfAs1UGjmRGoEH_n5pvwT19ns3EJIylW9S34zlw1BapeVA&oe=6552EB2E', 'https://scontent-ord5-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/242353138_4860729567310795_4549382895650819283_n.jpg?stp=cp0_dst-jpg_e15_q65_s320x320&_nc_cat=102&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=5f2048&efg=eyJpIjoidCJ9&_nc_ohc=4i5MvpdXIisAX8fQJ7-&_nc_ht=scontent-ord5-2.xx&oh=00_AfAK1-U1MnCu98_naZbN6fVEvUnffkiExt8HZFwiQtbSIQ&oe=6552EB2E', ['https://scontent-ord5-2.xx.f