Salam and and greetings. Bangladesh Student Association, SIU is going to organize a “Meet and Greet” event on 24th September, 2022 (Saturday), at CIU. Besides the introduction of new members, the event will also hold the election of new BSA committee members for the academic year 2022-23. Donations are requested for the program as following:\nSingle student $5\nStudents living with family in Carbondale: $10\nUse PayPal: mehediwriter@gmail.com\n\n\nIf you want to pay cash please contact:\nMostak Sumon 618-434-5634: For Evergreen Area\nAswad 618-434-7196 & Badhon: 618-4345514: For E Mill St. & S Wall St.\nSumaiya: 618-303-9113: For Ambassador Hall, Housing, Point, Edge and other areas\n\n\nElection\nBSA Executive Body and Responsibilities\n1. President: Decides on overall committee matters, coordinates with university body and other RSOs. President will preside over the meetings. (Graduate Students Only)\n2. Vice-President: Assists the President and performs his/her duties in the absence of the President (Graduate students only)\n3. Secretary: Performs official work and documentation of the organization. Lead the organization of events and maintain the organization's liaison with external organizations.\n4. Treasurer: Manages income and expenditure of the organization and keeps financial accounts.\n5. Information Secretary: Maintains internal communication, disseminate information to the members. Manage and oversee website and social media sites and online platforms.\n6. Executive Member: Advises the Committee. Assist the Secretary. Perform his/her duties in the absence of the Secretary.\nAll graduate and undergraduate students are requested to join the BSA Committee. Please reply in comment section or message to Shujon Mehedi Hasan asap if you are interested to join BSA executive body and let us know in which position. If more than one candidate is interested in a particular post, it goes to the direct election. Students, faculties, staffs and their 18+ family members can vote on the event day.", "Dear Members and Faculties,\nSalam and and greetings. Bangladesh Student Association, SIU is going to organize a “Meet and Greet” event on 24th September, 2022 (Saturday), at CIU. Besides the introduction of new members, the event will also hold the election of new BSA committee members for the academic year 2022-23. Donations are requested for the program as following:\nSingle student $5\nStudents living with family in Carbondale: $10\nUse PayPal: mehediwriter@gmail.com\n\n\nIf you want to pay cash please contact:\nMostak Sumon 618-434-5634: For Evergreen Area\nAswad 618-434-7196 & Badhon: 618-4345514: For E Mill St. & S Wall St.\nSumaiya: 618-303-9113: For Ambassador Hall, Housing, Point, Edge and other areas\n\n\nElection\nBSA Executive Body and Responsibilities\n1. President: Decides on overall committee matters, coordinates with university body and other RSOs. President will preside over the meetings. (Graduate Students Only)\n2. Vice-President: Assists the President and performs his/her duties in the absence of the President (Graduate students only)\n3. Secretary: Performs official work and documentation of the organization. Lead the organization of events and maintain the organization's liaison with external organizations.\n4. Treasurer: Manages income and expenditure of the organization and keeps financial accounts.\n5. Information Secretary: Maintains internal communication, disseminate information to the members. Manage and oversee website and social media sites and online platforms.\n6. Executive Member: Advises the Committee. Assist the Secretary. Perform his/her duties in the absence of the Secretary.\nAll graduate and undergraduate students are requested to join the BSA Committee. Please reply in comment section or message to Shujon Mehedi Hasan asap if you are interested to join BSA executive body and let us know in which position. If more than one candidate is interested in a particular post, it goes to the direct election. Students, faculties, staffs and their 18+ family members can vote on the event day.", None, None, datetime.datetime(2022, 9, 15, 14, 35, 45), 1663270545, None, 'https://scontent-ord5-2.xx.fbcdn.net/m1/v/t6/An_UvxJXg9tdnLU3Y5qjPi0200MLilhzPXUgxzGjQzUMaNcmjdZA6anyrngvkdub33NZzZhd51fpCAEzNHFhko5aKRFP5fS1w_lKwYrzcNLupv27.png?ccb=10-5&oh=00_AfBaIyI1GghPTHlZudMsYtMW_pWuCi6_JPXo0hOvwZ0xIg&oe=65761BB9&_nc_sid=7da55a', [], [], ['https://scontent-ord5-2.xx.fbcdn.net/m1/v/t6/An_UvxJXg9tdnLU3Y5qjPi0200MLilhzPXUgxzGjQzUMaNcmjdZA6anyrngvkdub33NZzZhd51fpCAEzNHFhko5aKRFP5fS1w_lKwYrzcNLupv27.png?ccb=10-5&oh=00_AfBaIyI1GghPTHlZudMsYtMW_pWuCi6_JPXo0hOvwZ0xIg&oe=65761BB9&_nc_sid=7da55a'], ['Like'], None, None, None, None, None, None, None, None, None, 2, 0, 0, 'https://m.facebook.com/groups/1590338747870221/permalink/3272611109642968/', None, [{'link': 'https://m.facebook.com/groups/1590338747870221/permalink/3272611109642968/?refid=18&paipv=0&eav=AfYsoBXh9_EYpPiJKTj7EGf2fjt0gwAMKJwDorbSZ1blQpJEuvknxhZRzAhfcYvLLS4', 'text': 'More'}, {'link': 'https://m.facebook.com/groups/1590338747870221/permalink/3272611109642968/?_ft_=encrypted_tracking_data.0AY-6YYaxeAoVeBpknq7fho5ug4By2Lud8KgYpuLpoEsnpLWurJx2mWrIrSz8tAbX0pZm0wP_QKEMyGv0cwgPmGkTlwGpVzn9K_Pij3ZtzG11gs1j3dbK0msZt3U5gU4c3ZcH9jj1Yt8AHcwJIXYa78D6oQViMcduPzn13tQ5IP4EvXgVua3NYu7dp5oBuGC4F0xTpvKT_RrwAmt6-ZvbzymIOcKGiHwwEAU8Y-Yry_3luG3wONDe6JngUg4WeOpQdNugPV4TU3hSl6TzIzxiX4_VxuXpngzzQfhThl15YtdDygzDKOLHSkdjcJiFMSNn_L_FpBfMNfxPTQZf4u6AlDVugQ7DpFRGcFXXOcI6V5O3QfnTBvRRtCT5lV__XUgyFLQ8RFxanYJaKqxYo1f0BYMQCxC70EGEyek-zIP9EZda9JGDV7j6cU_zKqtURne-\\-\\76oInQIY_n9QscC1InoYev2Ln5qUkO6TDVzIz9Di0WxYRoWI6lniGyPx0v_GmQpaHXv6xa3T8BwMhQ0aJb6gDR1eKtbfFauegrBQbapzowM_q47CNIbCr4NcgogXZfP8snqYAViu-D66gOAKKmq3QJu1VE9coQh6NsklTdcaOzp_gXzy67Z49wZYcVLbSxHTVwSRmh0CfrvL5Lxbtlnm_9FxtwVwtgE3vYN3osVJZnt13bhaEnlJPai9UnutS0HT3zyViiK10TrCleKDdwxeDaQ1ys1r-ujnn-Mp5N-wqa-QDES549PfyJk3xwsWBjpYbBntSRwNCFFilbCCK0CMniB92Cuq0_6kt0NHhCIKHTIalm-WFrnwCveuvtWbRgbYQqXzPRusP7Zhk