 Recent study at Yale University found that SKY Happiness Retreat significantly reduces stress, depression, and has a long-lasting impact on mental health, mindfulness, positive emotion, and social connectedness. The SKY Happiness Retreat introduces SKY Meditation, an evidence-based meditation practice integrated with breath work that can significantly increase one\'s well-being and calmness, and significantly reduces anxiety and stress markers. The course features interactive group processes, experiential learning, emotional intelligence training, breath-work, yoga, and evidence-based meditation. It\'s one of the coolest places to connect with yourself, make new friends, and most importantly, have fun! Participants will also have an option to attend workshops in Global Resilience and Wellbeing summit.\n\nWe\'re happy to share that the SKY Happiness Retreat is partially funded for students. SKY Happiness Retreat has limited spots. Availability is first-come-first serve, by registration only and requires attendance to all sessions.\n\nLocation: Online via Zoom\n\nTiming:\nApril 22nd (Fri) | 6 pm - 9 pm CST\nApril 23rd and 24th (Sat & Sun) | 10 am - 1 pm CST\n\nApply here: http://tiny.cc/skyglobalsummit (Applicants will go through a telephonic confirmation round only after which the registration process will be complete)"\n\nFor any questions, contact me or email diksha.mittal@iahv.org.', 'Hello All,\nPlease read the post below if you are interested in meditation, yoga and breath practice. Contact me if you like to know more in details.\n\n"To equip students with mental health tools and create positive social connections, we are hosting the SKY Happiness Retreat at SIUC and Global Wellbeing Summit on April 22-24th (online).\n\nIt is being offered as a partially funded program for SIU students. We have only 7 partial scholarship spots left.\n\nSKY Happiness Retreat\n\nSKY Happiness Retreat is a high-impact 9-hour total well-being training offered to thousands of university students, faculty, and staff across the country. Recent study at Yale University found that SKY Happiness Retreat significantly reduces stress, depression, and has a long-lasting impact on mental health, mindfulness, positive emotion, and social connectedness. The SKY Happiness Retreat introduces SKY Meditation, an evidence-based meditation practice integrated with breath work that can significantly increase one\'s well-being and calmness, and significantly reduces anxiety and stress markers. The course features interactive group processes, experiential learning, emotional intelligence training, breath-work, yoga, and evidence-based meditation. It\'s one of the coolest places to connect with yourself, make new friends, and most importantly, have fun! Participants will also have an option to attend workshops in Global Resilience and Wellbeing summit.\n\nWe\'re happy to share that the SKY Happiness Retreat is partially funded for students. SKY Happiness Retreat has limited spots. Availability is first-come-first serve, by registration only and requires attendance to all sessions.\n\nLocation: Online via Zoom\n\nTiming:\nApril 22nd (Fri) | 6 pm - 9 pm CST\nApril 23rd and 24th (Sat & Sun) | 10 am - 1 pm CST\n\nApply here: http://tiny.cc/skyglobalsummit (Applicants will go through a telephonic confirmation round only after which the registration process will be complete)"\n\nFor any questions, contact me or email diksha.mittal@iahv.org.', '', None, datetime.datetime(2022, 4, 19, 11, 10, 5), 1650384605, 'https://scontent-ord5-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/278525912_3124947881095403_110060307543772055_n.jpg?stp=cp0_dst-jpg_e15_fr_q65&_nc_cat=111&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=5f2048&efg=eyJpIjoidCJ9&_nc_ohc=j8UPwXC-9ncAX_fyv76&tn=PKBvE-4fpoK4f5Ih&_nc_ht=scontent-ord5-1.xx&oh=00_AfB9FWC77xXTLsEIOTqSvIwC8FFHWFn31BcV_ZDstY5Ifg&oe=6552A550&manual_redirect=1', 'https://scontent-ord5-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.30808-6/278525912_3124947881095403_110060307543772055_n.jpg?stp=cp0_dst-jpg_e15_p320x3