escnetQUgLY6F6roJnZn-7vMQmzIjj4GN3PrbzvXzQclrgPFQNRhtE5QoV-qLrrq_dRL5U5p8ausC-l88CAJZRP0SwaVYgE8VnROURjXEJ4x6kUTVzFlzNFtPlKjpHc0_aE2nHw_uKi-tinlNzluVCGYXiQk5xNXPJ4wS3XKSd0OLReIskyKMnCY8BIgM58nll0OoZ2-EVWC7dmf7YQEgiJ4CQ32E2ifIqXxj83VygWu7CllvvvnMnSuiS7U1VAXq59aO5nX4n0ydqO2YYZN36IjbGweUj10CPl34kUxqedkOLDzCL_02D0guzv_YorFEDy7bIcQwy_xG3ZBXrypz4Ehvfn3W40lJcpkFewi_y3YtUjZ4v-JbDWgp58luGPuXVXuJRfvzRLntXp7M0M2xLgiRPZYsDH3JDwB9RVaMJtMglFJioRDM5ZnnIH_H0KwAMlofk431GrtYqGyrLUwrcL9H5pFx2V5yna3esIWJ68yEi7MuYJuxnKln-1F0FySe5-\\-\\BAubBEdg5h-48VXF6yxy-FlUxHVYUBVDgRyCwK04b4kZFP78SUiCejBSDp20clvFcMD_dSFmbPo0yliLH7AsxbxQpQzItkeAu-CbMjjONEpl0Z7Cqwpuqy1tFyd2MyTkRyZbfwh7BOemyrKAV3cH8awaKaXqnzHLzAhXLUybwIJUVWyOrGm1K5796MwwcjnHfbBQUlXrgUdvbttqKytfdIGKKBBsaGM0cj8k1myOLW7Jq4h6yWdp9QOdMqbqJp6mF5kLSjX8eOCXXE7iYuxS49Ah1-L1crzVR67OLGQDL82BsZkeuqVKH8i-ZcpF9d2Rcqm-YUT0fcQzMtSj1PptCZtaRdek5fb1M2lVsnwyyohSwzJ2KBOjgT46HhBEVT&__tn__=C-R&paipv=0', False, None, None, None, None, None, None, True, None, None, None, None, 8, None, None, None, None, [], False])dict_values(['3149686645268749', "Long post Alert!!!\n\nHello All,\nInternational festival week is from 4 to 8. We have our parade of flag on 4th, food festival on 6th and cultural show on 8th. Kind reminder that, food festival and cultural show both are competitions. There will be a winner country. Lets make sure that we are the winner country of this year.\n\nDetails of them :\n\nParade of flag:\nIt will start from CIE at 9 AM. Whoever wants to walk with our flag, please come to CIE within 8.50 AM. Everyone can join and no restrictions. Interested people please comment here, or contact Arunima Aindrila Badhon.\n\nFood Festival:\nWe selected 3 items; Shrimp Biriyani, lacchi, jhal muri, and estimated customer is 600. We got 2 hours on monday from 5pm-7pm and 2 hours on Tuesday from 5pm-7pm to cook our dishs and all cooking must be done in the student center kitchen area. We have already given a tour to it, and we came to the conclusion that to cook for 600 people within 4 hours, we need at least 20 people each day. We Know the time is bit odd during ramadan. We are well aware of it, thus, we will be providing Pizza, khejur, water and soft drinks to break our fasts. We kindly ask your assistance here. Even If you can come only for one day, you are most welcome. We believe, if we all come forward to make this seemingly difficult task possible, we can nail it. Interested people please contact Shujon Mehedi Hasan bhai.\nNow, we will sell food on Wednesday (6th) from 11 AM - 2 PM. It is mandatory that two (2) members must be present at the table latest by 10:45am to serve the food to attendees. As we all got classes, again we need more students here. 🙏\n\nI. e: We will earn money for our RSO through this food festival. Thus, Whoever will be working in the food festival, will get dinner treat by BSA after this festival. Thanks.\n\nLast year Bangladesh was the winner country of cooking show. We are hoping to be the winner again. ❣️\n\nCultural show:\nContents are chosen - fashion show, dance and an opening speech.\nFor Fashion show, we have decided some themes such as Farmers, Freedom fighter, Baul, Newly wedded couple, Modern couple, traditional 1900's couple, Tribal couple/ person etc. If you get more ideas, please share.\nFor dance, we need participants.\nThe entire cultural show duration is 10 minutes. Within this 10 minutes, we have to incorporate everything.\nThere will be practice session for 2 days from 6-10pm in student center Ball Room.\nAgain, there will be a winner country.\n\nFor any queries, please comment here or contact me, @Arunima or Muhammad Aswad Ali.\n\nThanks for your patience. See you all.", "Long post Alert!!!\n\nHello All,\nInternational festival week is from 4 to 8. We have our parade of flag on 4th, food festival on 6th and cultural show on 8th. Kind reminder that, food festival and cultural show both are competitions. There will be a winner country. Lets make sure that we are the winner country of this year.\n\nDetails of them :\n\nParade of flag:\nIt will start from CIE at 9 AM. Whoever wants to walk with our flag, please come to CIE within 8.50 AM. Everyone can join and no restrictions. Interested people please comment here, or contact Arunima Aindrila Badhon.\n\nFood Festival:\nWe selected 3 items; Shrimp Biriyani, lacchi, jhal muri, and estimated customer is 600. We got 2 hours on monday from 5pm-7pm and 2 hours on Tuesday from 5pm-7pm to cook our dishs and all cooking must be done in the student center kitchen area. We have already given a tour to it, and we came to the conclusion that to cook for 600 people within 4 hours, we need at least 20 people each day. We Know the time is bit odd during ramadan. We are well aware of it, thus, we will be providing Pizza, khejur, water and soft drinks to break our fasts. We kindly ask your assistance here. Even If you can come only for one day, you are most welcome. We believe, if we all come forward to make this seemingly difficult task possible, we can nail it. Interested people please contact Shujon Mehedi Hasan bhai.\nNow, we will sell food on Wednesday (6th) from 11 AM - 2 PM. It is mandatory that two (2) members must be present at the table latest by 10:45am to serve the food to attendees. As we all got classes, again we need more students here. 🙏\n\nI. e: We will earn money for our RSO through this food festival. Thus, Whoever will be working in the food festival, will get dinner treat by BSA after this festival. Thanks.\n\nLast year Bangladesh was the winner country of cooking show. We are hoping to be the winner again. ❣️\n\nCultural show:\nContents are chosen - fashion show, dance and an opening speech.\nFor Fashion show, we have decided some themes such as Farmers, Freedom fighter, Baul, Newly wedded couple, Modern couple, traditional 1900's couple, Tribal couple/ person etc. If you get more ideas, please share.\nFor dance, we need participants.\nThe entire cultural show duration is 10 minutes. Within this 10 minutes, we have to incorporate everything.\nThere will be practice session for 2 days from 6-10pm in student center Ball Room.\nAgain, there will be a winner country.\n\nFor any queries, please comment here or contact me, @Arunima or Muhammad Aswad Ali.\n\nThanks for your patience. See you all.", '', None, datetime.datetime(2022, 4, 3, 13, 14, 12), 1649009652, None, 'https://scontent-ord5-2.xx.fbcdn.net/m1/v/t6/An_UvxJXg9tdnLU3Y5qjPi0200MLilhzPXUgxzGjQzUMaNcmjdZA6anyrngvkdub33NZzZhd51fpCAEzNHFhko5aKRFP5fS1w_lKwYrzcNLupv27.png?ccb=10-5&oh=00_AfBaIyI1GghPTHlZudMsYtMW_pWuCi6_JPXo0hOvwZ0xIg&oe=65761BB9&_nc_sid=7da55a', [], [], ['https://scontent-ord5-2.xx.fbcdn.net/m1/v/t6/An_UvxJXg9tdnLU3Y5qjPi0200MLilhzPXUgxzGjQzUMaNcmjdZA6anyrngvkdub33NZzZhd51fpCAEzNHFhko5aKRFP5fS1w_lKwYrzcNLupv27.png?ccb=10-5&oh=00_AfBaIyI1GghPTHlZudMsYtMW_pWuCi6_JPXo0hOvwZ0xIg&oe=65761BB9&_nc_sid=7da55a', 'https://scontent-ord5-2.xx.fbcdn.net/m1/v/t6/An_0KlxkBZwTJgSV9p2pDQkaZcuO9nFP4R72nyZmCnWKIxG_MSUbtZ_uBFHkKhQVvjgeou7ijfWCAKaRfSRFqQS9RcziMUL4BTtfpxJ2KfylUgpq.png?ccb=10-5&oh=00_AfDnn3XL6Zz5M57h3NPR8zC1mhXPIs5GD_5LZRnnXWSYlg&oe=65763113&_nc_sid=7da55a'], ['Like', 'Wow'], None, None, None, None, None, None, None, None, None, 6, 2, 0, 'https://m.facebook.com/groups/1590338747870221/permalink/3149686645268749/', None, [{'link': 'https://m.facebook.com/groups/1590338747870221/permalink/3149686645268749/?refid=18&paipv=0&eav=AfYeQ9GXGIU5SOKgFTkntYo3-5E8mVqrLEUxisD046ytt37eq2YFIyG2KPw0WDahvp8', 'text': 'More'}, {'link': '/profile.php?id=100009785553848&groupid=1590338747870221&eav=AfbpCkcy2TRMMijsc0NcLYtYLon_lwFQ735eR2y4ddOsOpF5nYNRZTAnCeJX636fmKk&refid=18&_ft_=encrypted_tracking_data.0AY_v5ofIH_QSa4KU8AcCbh-Q9Fl41wApUfbPUeeNEBfx9qlrfVUXOuRH4_ifC_Ou-JDmiLQSwpHrp1Ph-sKgulakRC4TXxw2zK3w0FwQ6AXIKxdjxDqdw29HDh7jcA8fkRXZguSvrdCVY_y89oLjvzxmZ4wxNGZx-S8pP1i0_BPph4575VhgiSQw2ve1ogQWdm3KhFnyDVNcShr5sB9E659vwUinJy6JStIdjFGzfJXgJAkmeeTgnDlKGNFVAEW789GRQMZBxgWlLmtZJUq7VH8noSlyrgDhT_xgvByYTBIHIEs9S05L5